fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data

Class PersistenceBackendFactoryRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.PersistenceBackendFactoryRegistry

  • public class PersistenceBackendFactoryRegistry
extends Object
    The registry that holds registered URI schemes with their associated PersistenceBackendFactory.

    This PersistenceBackendFactoryRegistry is used for dynamically create PersistentStore and PersistenceBackend when loading and saving a PersistentResource. For this reason, a PersistenceBackendFactory must be registered before using these operations, with the register(String, PersistenceBackendFactory) method.

    See Also:
    Resource.load(Map), Resource.save(Map)
